    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-17T11:14:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-17T11:14:00-05:00" n="398"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d398">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 822.00/377.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Hartman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-17T11:00:00-05:14">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 17, 1914, 11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I am informed by the Minister for Foreign Affairs that the port of Esmeraldas is
                    again open to commerce, the city having been captured by the Government forces.
                    President Plaza is expected to arrive in Quito March 19.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hartman</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
